description: {"blocks":[{"key":"405jc","text":"This protocol details a step by step method to prepare pure fractions of synaptosomes for biochemical analysis. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"474dq","text":"Pre-chill the homogeniser and buffers on ice. Weigh the tissue","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b6thr","text":"Add 4x volume of ice-cold homogenizing buffer to glass homogenizers","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"di5tp","text":"Apply 12 strokes of even tension with the homogeniser rod","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cna7a","text":"Transfer to 1.5ml tube (original tube)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d9ldn","text":"Determine which tissue has the smallest volume and use that volume for all samples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7uboh","text":"Centrifuge at 1,000g for 10mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6daaq","text":"Transfer the supernatant into fresh 1.5ml tube and spin at 12,500g for 15mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e694g","text":"Discard supernatant carefully","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77nlf","text":"Resuspend pellet in 1ml of H-buffer, transfer to fresh glass homogenizer and mash for 6 strokes even tension","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"81std","text":"In polypropylene/ultra-clear tube add 5ml of 1.2M sucrose","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2uj77","text":"Slowly and steadily add in 5ml of 0.8M sucrose to create clear/distinct gradient","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5rl4d","text":"Overlay sample on top of gradient","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9obg2","text":"Weigh sucrose gradient tubes (add H-buffer if weight is off by more than 0.05g)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"96kr3","text":"Centrifuge with slow accleration and zero brake in 4 degrees at 23,600g for 70 mins in a SW41 rotor","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1qdi2","text":"Using syringe, extract synaptosome layer between 0.8M and 1.2M sucrose and transfer into fresh 1.5ml tubes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5l5dv","text":"Plate sample with appropriate dilutions into 24-well plate (dilute with H-buffer or PBS)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"572qe","text":"Spin in 4°C, max speed ~4,000 rpm for 20mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"imq2","text":"Remove liquid and fix in 4% PFA for 20mins on rocker/shaker for 20mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3l66a","text":"Wash x2~3 with PNBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"90hsk","text":"Either cover and place in fridge or move directly to immunofluorescence protocol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Fractionation of synaptosomes
